casebody.data:
Willie James BARNES, Jr., Petitioner-Appellant, v. Louie L. WAINWRIGHT, Director, Division of Corrections, State of Florida, Respondent-Appellee. No. 71-2485

Summary Calendar.*

United States Court of Appeals, Fifth Circuit. Feb. 28, 1972.

Before THORNBERRY, MORGAN and CLARK, Circuit Judges.

Rule 18, 5th Cir.; see Isbell Enterprises, Inc. v. Citizens Casualty Co. of New York et al., 5th Cir. 1970, 431 F.2d 409, Part I.

 PER CURIAM:

Affirmed. See Local Rule 21.1, 2

. See NLRB v. Amalgamated Clothing Workers of America, 5 Cir. 1970, 430 F.2d 966.

. This habeas corpus petitioner alleges the State prosecutor knowingly used perjured testimony to obtain his conviction.
